WEBVTT

00:06.702 --> 00:07.050
.

00:07.094 --> 00:09.009
- A group of us
were driving home.

00:09.052 --> 00:10.140
We saw you
by the side of the road.

00:10.184 --> 00:11.924
- And there was the girl.
- What girl?

00:11.968 --> 00:13.535
- Ella Jones, she's an artist.

00:13.578 --> 00:16.538
- Wherever Ella is,
she's connected to that place.

00:16.581 --> 00:21.804
- Go back to the beginning,
Gavin, November 16, 1988.

00:21.847 --> 00:23.545
- Aldridge!

00:25.808 --> 00:28.158
- Did you see what hurt Eddie?
- It was an old man.

00:28.202 --> 00:30.552
He had something on his back,
a handprint.

00:30.595 --> 00:32.293
- You're the Sky People.
- What?

00:32.336 --> 00:34.730
- My grandfather told me
about you.

00:34.773 --> 00:37.298
- Stop! Let them go, Silas.

00:37.341 --> 00:38.821
- I still don't know your name.

00:38.864 --> 00:42.738
- Para.
- Veronica!

00:42.781 --> 00:44.044
- We're in the Ice Age,

00:44.087 --> 00:46.437
and with that came
violent winter storms.

00:56.186 --> 00:58.580
- Okay.

01:00.538 --> 01:03.280
- Great,
mushrooms are drenched.

01:03.324 --> 01:04.716
- There goes breakfast.

01:04.760 --> 01:08.198
- Oh, damn it.

01:11.941 --> 01:14.813
- Hey.

01:14.857 --> 01:16.076
- Good morning.

01:16.119 --> 01:17.164
- Brought you this.

01:19.905 --> 01:22.908
I--I just wanted to say
thank you again

01:22.952 --> 01:25.563
for having my back yesterday.

01:25.607 --> 01:28.436
It really meant a lot.
- Of course.

01:31.743 --> 01:34.398
- I like what you've done
with the place.

01:34.442 --> 01:36.400
- Yeah, doesn't look like
we're getting out of here

01:36.444 --> 01:40.883
anytime soon,
need some place to call home.

01:40.926 --> 01:43.146
- You know, you don't
have to stay here.

01:43.190 --> 01:45.105
There's plenty of room
on the bus.

01:46.367 --> 01:49.109
- I think it's best
if I stay here.

01:51.589 --> 01:53.243
- Okay.

01:56.942 --> 01:58.466
- Hey.

02:04.602 --> 02:07.388
I'm really glad you're here.

02:08.519 --> 02:10.478
- Me too.

02:28.496 --> 02:29.584
- I'm trying to wrap my head
around what the hell

02:29.627 --> 02:31.368
you're doing,
but I've got no idea.

02:31.412 --> 02:33.805
- Well, we're lucky that storm
wasn't worse.

02:33.849 --> 02:35.720
And every time we need food
we can't keep risking

02:35.764 --> 02:37.505
our lives
going into the woods, right?

02:37.548 --> 02:42.162
So drumroll, please,
we're building a greenhouse.

02:42.205 --> 02:43.815
- With windshields.
- Yeah.

02:43.859 --> 02:45.121
I saw it on YouTube once.

02:45.165 --> 02:48.211
Who know
hit would come in handy?

02:48.255 --> 02:51.258
NO, no, no, no, no, no!

02:51.301 --> 02:53.303
- Damn. I'm sorry, man.

02:53.347 --> 02:54.652
- If we don't figure out
how to live off the land,

02:54.696 --> 02:56.828
we're never going
to survive out here.

02:56.872 --> 02:58.352
- We're so screwed.

03:18.110 --> 03:19.895
- Help.
- Damn it.

03:19.938 --> 03:24.769
- Ty! Ty! Help, please!

03:24.813 --> 03:26.554
Help!

03:26.597 --> 03:29.121
Ty!

03:29.165 --> 03:31.341
- Down this way.
- Please, come back.

03:31.385 --> 03:33.691
- Lilly, what's wrong?
Where's Ty?

03:33.735 --> 03:35.867
- We heard someone in the
woods; he went after them.

03:35.911 --> 03:38.305
- What if it's Veronica?
What if she hurts him again?

03:38.348 --> 03:39.349
- We are not going
to let that happen.

03:39.393 --> 03:40.785
- Come on, let's fan out.

03:40.829 --> 03:42.352
Stay in pairs;
nobody goes out there alone.

03:42.396 --> 03:45.050
- Come with me. Come on.

03:45.094 --> 03:47.270
- Ty!
- Ty!

03:47.314 --> 03:49.272
- Ty.

03:49.316 --> 03:51.274
- Ty!

03:51.318 --> 03:52.319
- Ty.

03:52.362 --> 03:54.930
[footsteps thumping]

03:54.973 --> 03:57.585
- Did you hear that?

04:00.327 --> 04:02.720
Hey!

04:02.764 --> 04:04.461
Stop!

04:04.505 --> 04:07.421
[tense music]

04:07.464 --> 04:09.031
♪

04:09.074 --> 04:10.206
- Ahh!

04:10.250 --> 04:12.948
[gasping]

04:12.991 --> 04:16.734
- Whoa, hey.

04:16.778 --> 04:18.170
- [grunts]

04:18.214 --> 04:20.434
- What's he doing out here?

04:20.477 --> 04:24.960
♪

04:25.003 --> 04:27.963
[dramatic music]

04:28.006 --> 04:29.965
♪

04:37.494 --> 04:39.061
All right, pal.

04:39.104 --> 04:41.324
Looks like you'll survive.

04:41.368 --> 04:43.761
- See, told you
it wouldn't hurt.

04:46.068 --> 04:47.330
- What brought you down here?

04:49.463 --> 04:52.074
- Hey, you're not in trouble.

04:55.773 --> 04:57.993
- Riley, his wound is cleaned;
why don't you dress it outside?

04:58.036 --> 04:59.603
- Sure.

04:59.647 --> 05:02.563
Come on.

05:04.086 --> 05:06.958
- Hey, I'm Lilly.

05:07.002 --> 05:08.090
It's nice to meet you.

05:11.615 --> 05:14.662
- So how long do you think
he's been spying on us?

05:15.706 --> 05:18.230
- Spying? He's a child.

05:18.274 --> 05:19.406
- I know the kid
helped us once,

05:19.449 --> 05:21.451
but his grandfather
did try to kill us.

05:21.495 --> 05:23.323
- Yeah, because we broke
into their home.

05:23.366 --> 05:25.325
- Exactly. So he probably
sees us a threat,

05:25.368 --> 05:26.804
and they sent the kid
to gather intel.

05:26.848 --> 05:28.545
- Come on,
you can't be serious.

05:28.589 --> 05:30.982
- Insurgents use kids to gather
intel; it's not so far-fetched.

05:31.026 --> 05:32.941
- From my experience with Para,
I'd say her people

05:32.984 --> 05:34.986
are more afraid of us
than we are of them.

05:35.030 --> 05:37.511
- Uh, dude, they tied us up,
put is in a room with a person

05:37.554 --> 05:40.383
who'd been electrocuted.
Just like that guy, Eddie.

05:40.427 --> 05:41.776
- I know that woman
took care of you,

05:41.819 --> 05:43.473
but we can't forget
what happened to him.

05:43.517 --> 05:45.083
- No, we can't.

05:45.127 --> 05:47.434
But Para was convinced
the kid's grandfather

05:47.477 --> 05:48.826
had nothing to do with it.

05:48.870 --> 05:50.524
You know, Lilly saw him
after Eddie was killed.

05:50.567 --> 05:52.569
Someone else
could have done it.

05:52.613 --> 05:54.919
- Regardless, it's a problem
the kid got so close

05:54.963 --> 05:56.356
to the clearing
without us knowing.

05:56.399 --> 05:59.271
- Maybe it's not a problem.

05:59.315 --> 06:02.579
Maybe it's a solution.

06:02.623 --> 06:04.015
- What does that mean?

06:04.059 --> 06:05.843
- All of our resources
were wiped out by the storm.

06:05.887 --> 06:08.106
The kid is hurt.
It's dangerous in the woods.

06:08.150 --> 06:09.891
And he needs help
getting back to his home.

06:09.934 --> 06:12.067
We need help trying
to figure out how to survive.

06:12.110 --> 06:13.851
Clearly his people know
how to do that.

06:13.895 --> 06:16.376
- Right, a diplomatic mission.

06:16.419 --> 06:17.899
- I don't think
that's a good idea.

06:17.942 --> 06:19.683
- I do. We need to make peace
with Para's village.

06:19.727 --> 06:21.772
This could be a first step.

06:21.816 --> 06:23.513
- Yeah, and if they don't
see it that way?

06:23.557 --> 06:26.429
- We'll have to make sure
they do.

06:26.473 --> 06:29.911
We can head there now.
Ty? Levi?

06:29.954 --> 06:33.001
- All right. We'll stay here
and set up a patrol.

06:33.044 --> 06:34.176
- Good luck, team.

06:34.219 --> 06:35.743
- Thanks.

06:43.359 --> 06:45.013
- Is this your first time
in a car?

06:45.056 --> 06:46.884
What do you think?

06:46.928 --> 06:49.409
- It's fun.
- [laughs]

06:50.584 --> 06:52.412
- What's your name?

06:54.805 --> 06:59.070
Okay, I'll go first. I'm Eve.

06:59.114 --> 07:00.507
- Isaiah.

07:00.550 --> 07:03.074
- This is my friend, Ty.
This is Levi.

07:03.118 --> 07:04.685
- I'm impressed.

07:04.728 --> 07:06.077
Made it all the way
from your village to our camp.

07:06.121 --> 07:07.731
That's quite a hike.

07:07.775 --> 07:09.472
But I'm guessing
you've done it before.

07:09.516 --> 07:10.952
- A bunch of times.

07:10.995 --> 07:13.433
I saw you
when you first got here,

07:13.476 --> 07:16.261
then when you found your son.

07:16.305 --> 07:17.915
I didn't mean to spy,

07:17.959 --> 07:20.614
I just wanted to make sure
you weren't hurt.

07:22.790 --> 07:25.532
- That's really lovely;
thank you.

07:25.575 --> 07:27.098
So when you saw us
at the fork--

07:27.142 --> 07:29.100
- I knew you weren't dangerous.
You weren't anything like

07:29.144 --> 07:31.625
what my grandfather says
about the Sky People.

07:31.668 --> 07:33.888
- What does your grandfather
say about the Sky People?

07:36.064 --> 07:37.631
- That you're our enemy.

07:40.938 --> 07:43.114
- Levi, we have to keep going.

07:43.158 --> 07:45.508
I told you this was a bad idea.
I'm turning around.

07:45.552 --> 07:48.206
- Levi. Levi, stop!

07:48.250 --> 07:51.209
[tense music]

07:51.253 --> 07:55.866
♪

07:59.348 --> 07:59.479
.

07:59.522 --> 08:02.482
[tense music]

08:02.525 --> 08:09.489
♪

08:11.142 --> 08:12.622
- Where are you taking us?

08:12.666 --> 08:19.890
♪

08:20.761 --> 08:23.328
- What's going on here?
- Found them in the woods.

08:23.372 --> 08:24.765
What should we do with them?

08:24.808 --> 08:27.507
- Para, you're their leader?

08:27.550 --> 08:29.770
Please, tell them
we mean no harm.

08:29.813 --> 08:31.249
- You know him?

08:31.293 --> 08:32.599
- I helped Ty during the storm.

08:32.642 --> 08:35.384
- This is Eve and Levi,
my friends.

08:35.427 --> 08:37.473
- Isaiah!

08:42.260 --> 08:44.611
What's all this about?

08:44.654 --> 08:47.048
- I fell.

08:47.091 --> 08:48.745
- We found him
outside our clearing.

08:48.789 --> 08:51.313
He hurt his wrist, and we just
wanted to get him home safely.

08:51.356 --> 08:53.924
- I told you to stop
going back to that place.

08:53.968 --> 08:55.839
- I know.
I'm sorry, Grandpa.

08:55.883 --> 08:57.145
- You can let them go.

08:57.188 --> 08:59.669
We appreciate you bringing
Isaiah back to us.

08:59.713 --> 09:01.279
But it would be best
if you leave.

09:01.323 --> 09:02.367
- Para, please.

09:04.979 --> 09:06.589
We don't know how
to work the land,

09:06.633 --> 09:09.331
how to build shelter,
how to protect ourselves.

09:09.374 --> 09:10.767
We barely made it
through the storm.

09:10.811 --> 09:12.334
Next time it could be worse.

09:12.377 --> 09:14.423
We were just hoping that--

09:14.466 --> 09:16.120
that you might be willing
to teach us.

09:16.164 --> 09:18.688
- They trespass in my village.

09:18.732 --> 09:21.735
We can't trust them.

09:21.778 --> 09:23.606
- If you don't help us,
we won't make it.

09:26.740 --> 09:29.394
We're just trying to keep
our people alive.

09:35.662 --> 09:37.402
- Maybe there's
something we can do.

09:39.709 --> 09:40.754
- Thank you.

09:43.974 --> 09:46.586
[indistinct chatter]

09:47.978 --> 09:50.198
- Hey.
- Hey.

09:50.241 --> 09:52.417
- I hear your dad
is pairing people up,

09:52.461 --> 09:54.245
have them go on patrol.

09:54.289 --> 09:58.249
- Yeah, that's the word.
- Scott and Lucas paired up.

09:58.293 --> 10:00.556
What do you say
we do the same?

10:00.600 --> 10:03.037
- Yeah, I wouldn't mind that.

10:03.080 --> 10:05.692
- Riley, can I talk to you?

10:05.735 --> 10:07.868
- Uh, sure.

10:07.911 --> 10:12.568
- Give us a minute, Josh?

10:12.612 --> 10:14.004
- I don't want you
partnering with him.

10:14.048 --> 10:15.397
- Why not?

10:15.440 --> 10:16.833
- I see the way you two
look at each other.

10:16.877 --> 10:19.575
You'll get distracted.
- No, we won't.

10:19.619 --> 10:22.230
- Could you just do
what I say, please?

10:22.273 --> 10:24.449
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

10:24.493 --> 10:27.235
Eddie was murdered out there
a few days ago.

10:27.278 --> 10:28.584
I'm just trying
to keep you safe.

10:28.628 --> 10:30.020
- Well, it wasn't
a problem yesterday

10:30.064 --> 10:33.415
when I drove into a storm
and you didn't say a word.

10:33.458 --> 10:35.504
- This is different.
- No, it's not.

10:35.547 --> 10:37.245
You act like you care
about me one minute,

10:37.288 --> 10:39.377
and the next minute
you couldn't care less.

10:39.421 --> 10:43.338
Honestly, I'm tired of it.

10:44.034 --> 10:45.340
- Come on, Josh.

10:49.997 --> 10:51.825
- It's been a week
since the massive sinkhole

10:51.868 --> 10:53.609
opened
in the middle of Los Angeles.

10:53.653 --> 10:55.089
- You've reached
Dr. Sophia Nathan.

10:55.132 --> 10:56.699
Please leave a message.

10:56.743 --> 11:00.660
- Hey, Sophia, it's Gavin.
Just call me when you can.

11:06.578 --> 11:07.797
- I'm really glad you're here.

11:09.581 --> 11:10.539
- Me too.

11:12.846 --> 11:14.369
- [exhales]

11:17.851 --> 11:19.069
[sighs]

11:19.113 --> 11:20.418
[door shuts]

11:22.812 --> 11:24.161
- Going to school.

11:25.510 --> 11:27.295
- Wait. I'll--I'll drive you.

11:27.338 --> 11:30.124
- No, thanks.
- Iz, hold up.

11:30.167 --> 11:32.735
- You wanted us to go back
to normal and move on, right?

11:32.779 --> 11:35.129
Normally I get to school
on time, so I got to go.

11:35.172 --> 11:37.697
- Look, hey, hey.

11:37.740 --> 11:40.482
I know you think I'm giving up.

11:40.525 --> 11:42.136
But it's for the best.

11:42.179 --> 11:44.181
[phone buzzing]

11:47.315 --> 11:48.838
- Who's that?

11:48.882 --> 11:52.494
- Just a construction job
I applied for.

11:52.537 --> 11:54.714
- Uh-huh, you better
take it, then.

11:58.021 --> 12:00.981
- [sighs]

12:01.024 --> 12:03.331
Sophia?
- I couldn't track down Ella,

12:03.374 --> 12:05.072
but I did speak
to her assistant.

12:05.115 --> 12:06.508
She'll be at the art gallery
at 9:00.

12:06.551 --> 12:07.552
She agreed to meet us.

12:07.596 --> 12:10.425
- Great. I'll meet you there.

12:10.468 --> 12:12.993
- So this sculpture,
Ella made it?

12:13.036 --> 12:14.690
- Yeah, it's a new piece.

12:14.734 --> 12:16.997
She only started it
six days ago.

12:17.040 --> 12:18.868
She's been obsessing over it.

12:18.912 --> 12:20.565
It's pretty incredible.

12:20.609 --> 12:22.132
- Can I give you my card?

12:22.176 --> 12:23.830
We'd love to talk to Ella
about the piece.

12:23.873 --> 12:25.788
- I'm not sure that
will be possible.

12:25.832 --> 12:27.137
- What do you mean?

12:27.181 --> 12:29.879
- Ella's been keeping
a low profile recently.

12:29.923 --> 12:31.751
She's not been herself.

12:31.794 --> 12:35.145
Honestly, she hasn't wanted
to talk to anyone.

12:35.189 --> 12:37.626
- We'd really appreciate
if you could try.

12:44.067 --> 12:46.896
- Hey, are you doing all right?

12:48.593 --> 12:51.031
- To be honest, not great.

12:51.074 --> 12:52.902
But I know Diana
would have wanted me to help.

12:52.946 --> 12:55.644
- If it gets too hard,
you just say the word.

13:03.565 --> 13:05.262
- Wait, whoa, wait.

13:07.612 --> 13:09.179
I think that's Ella.

13:09.223 --> 13:10.354
Ella.

13:10.398 --> 13:13.227
Hey, wait. Hey, wait!

13:13.270 --> 13:16.230
[tense music]

13:16.273 --> 13:18.319
♪

13:22.627 --> 13:22.976
.

13:23.019 --> 13:25.369
- Thank you for agreeing
to help us, Para.

13:25.413 --> 13:27.719
- I appreciate you bringing
Isaiah home safely.

13:27.763 --> 13:29.199
- Where are you taking us?

13:29.243 --> 13:32.333
- You'll see.
It's just up ahead.

13:34.465 --> 13:35.684
- Look, I know
what you're thinking.

13:35.727 --> 13:37.425
But we came here
for their help.

13:37.468 --> 13:38.905
We need to leave this alone.

13:38.948 --> 13:40.558
- I thought Eddie
was your friend.

13:40.602 --> 13:42.865
The dead man we found here
had the same markings,

13:42.909 --> 13:44.649
and I was sent
to bring him home.

13:44.693 --> 13:46.303
I can't let that go,
how can you?

13:46.347 --> 13:48.784
- I'm not. But the burden
of proof is on us.

13:48.828 --> 13:50.177
Without it, we stay the course.

13:50.220 --> 13:51.874
- These people could be
sheltering a killer.

13:51.918 --> 13:53.397
And if they are,

13:53.441 --> 13:55.486
I don't know how we trust
anything from them.

14:00.840 --> 14:02.493
- Here we are.

14:02.537 --> 14:06.019
This garden will help feed us
for an entire year.

14:06.062 --> 14:07.237
- This is amazing.

14:07.281 --> 14:09.109
- We can help you plant
your own garden.

14:09.152 --> 14:11.894
We can also show you how to
build a Kiki, our structures,

14:11.938 --> 14:14.462
and how to trade
with nearby villages.

14:14.505 --> 14:16.551
- Wait, there's other villages
down here?

14:16.594 --> 14:18.031
- Yes, many.

14:18.074 --> 14:19.119
We're happy
to make introductions

14:19.162 --> 14:20.250
when the time is right.

14:20.294 --> 14:21.425
- You're going above
and beyond,

14:21.469 --> 14:25.342
and we're grateful,
but why help us?

14:27.954 --> 14:30.565
- We weren't always
a peaceful village.

14:30.608 --> 14:32.872
I'd prefer to have you
as friends rather than enemies.

14:32.915 --> 14:34.874
- So would we.
- Of course.

14:34.917 --> 14:37.615
But Isaiah said Sky People
were your enemy.

14:37.659 --> 14:39.530
- They were.

14:39.574 --> 14:42.969
For generations we were
the only ones living here.

14:43.012 --> 14:45.797
And then 60 years ago
everything changed.

14:45.841 --> 14:47.408
- What happened?

14:47.451 --> 14:49.192
- A sinkhole opened
in the ocean.

14:49.236 --> 14:51.542
A passenger ship fell through.

14:51.586 --> 14:54.241
And the survivors came ashore.

14:54.284 --> 14:55.938
We tried to make peace
with them,

14:55.982 --> 14:57.635
but they didn't want that.

14:57.679 --> 15:02.466
After years of war those who
survived found common ground.

15:02.510 --> 15:06.949
Since then we've all lived
together, shared our cultures,

15:06.993 --> 15:09.691
our languages, our traditions.

15:09.734 --> 15:10.910
- It's incredible.

15:12.955 --> 15:15.131
- Eve,
we're going to have lunch.

15:15.175 --> 15:16.741
Can they stay, Para?

15:16.785 --> 15:19.309
- If they'd like.
- We'd love to.

15:22.965 --> 15:25.663
- Come on, Levi.

15:25.707 --> 15:28.666
[bell rings]

15:28.710 --> 15:32.670
- Thanks.

15:32.714 --> 15:36.457
- Hey, Izzy.

15:36.500 --> 15:37.371
We have English together.

15:37.414 --> 15:39.851
- Ah, yeah, of course, my bad.

15:39.895 --> 15:42.811
- No worries. I'm Andrew Veles.

15:42.854 --> 15:48.860
My sister, Riley, and my dad,
I lost them in the sinkhole.

15:48.904 --> 15:51.298
- I'm sorry.
- Yeah.

15:51.341 --> 15:54.214
I heard about
what happened to your family.

15:54.257 --> 15:56.172
Hard being here, isn't it?

15:56.216 --> 15:59.697
- Yeah. My dad says it'll
help me, but I don't see how.

15:59.741 --> 16:01.351
- My mom said the same thing.

16:01.395 --> 16:03.005
I know she means well,
but it's like she doesn't know

16:03.049 --> 16:05.138
how to be honest
with me anymore.

16:05.181 --> 16:07.096
You know what I mean?

16:07.140 --> 16:09.359
- Yeah, I do.

16:09.403 --> 16:12.449
- Anyway, one thing that's been
really good for me

16:12.493 --> 16:16.018
is talking to there
people going through it.

16:16.062 --> 16:19.108
There's a vigil later today;
you should come.

16:20.457 --> 16:23.373
- Thanks, but it's not for me.
- Think about it.

16:23.417 --> 16:25.027
[bell rings]

16:25.071 --> 16:27.551
- Got to get to class.

16:28.639 --> 16:31.033
- Take care, Izzy.

16:35.342 --> 16:36.386
- [sighs]

16:40.347 --> 16:43.176
- Want to talk about it?
- Not really.

16:43.219 --> 16:45.221
- Good. I hate when we talk

16:45.265 --> 16:49.660
about our parents anyway,
always ruins the mood.

16:49.704 --> 16:52.924
- We're out here trying to
make sure no one murders us.

16:52.968 --> 16:54.317
What kind of mood
are you going for?

16:54.361 --> 16:58.756
- The one that makes you smile.

16:58.800 --> 17:01.368
- It's a great smile.

17:01.411 --> 17:04.588
- You really are
such a dork sometimes.

17:04.632 --> 17:08.375
- Whatever.
You love the compliments.

17:08.418 --> 17:10.942
- I'm not against them
in theory,

17:10.986 --> 17:13.423
but we're supposed
to be patrolling.

17:13.467 --> 17:15.686
- Right.
- So we should stay focused.

17:15.730 --> 17:20.474
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

17:22.128 --> 17:25.609
- Well, I don't see anyone
out here,

17:25.653 --> 17:28.264
so I think we're safe.

17:30.832 --> 17:34.096
- Are you really going
to kiss me right now?

17:34.140 --> 17:37.099
- Is that okay?
- Yeah.

17:38.883 --> 17:41.799
[gentle piano music]

17:41.843 --> 17:49.024
♪

17:54.595 --> 17:55.770
- What are you doing out here,
sweetie?

17:55.813 --> 17:58.729
- Just passing out water.
I wanted to help.

17:58.773 --> 18:00.209
- Well, thank you.

18:00.253 --> 18:01.906
But you should get back
to the clearing.

18:01.950 --> 18:03.212
It's not safe for you out here.

18:05.997 --> 18:08.957
[ominous music]

18:09.000 --> 18:13.004
♪

18:13.048 --> 18:17.008
[branch cracks]

18:17.052 --> 18:19.098
- Hi, Lilly.

18:23.667 --> 18:23.841
.

18:23.885 --> 18:25.887
- Aren't you glad to see me?

18:25.930 --> 18:29.108
- Of course I am.
- Doesn't look that way.

18:30.283 --> 18:31.458
- Where have you been?

18:31.501 --> 18:33.460
- Looking for a place
we can stay.

18:33.503 --> 18:35.636
- I found a cave nearby;
it's safe.

18:35.679 --> 18:37.072
No one will find us.

18:37.116 --> 18:38.987
- Veronica,
I can't go with you.

18:39.030 --> 18:40.728
- Why not?
- You hurt Ty.

18:40.771 --> 18:42.121
- Yeah, well, he wanted
to keep us apart.

18:42.164 --> 18:43.209
I wasn't going
to let that happen.

18:43.252 --> 18:45.167
- [indistinct].

18:45.211 --> 18:47.865
- Lilly, we don't have time;
we have to go.

18:47.909 --> 18:48.910
- No.

18:48.953 --> 18:50.825
- Lilly, now.
- Hey! Wait.

18:50.868 --> 18:52.174
What the hell?
- Hey, let go of me.

18:52.218 --> 18:54.611
- That is not happening.
- What's going on here?

18:54.655 --> 18:56.483
- Just found this one trying
to sneak back in.

18:56.526 --> 18:57.919
- Let me go.

18:57.962 --> 18:59.355
- So you can come back
and try to take her again?

18:59.399 --> 19:01.444
- I would never hurt her.
You have to believe me.

19:01.488 --> 19:02.445
Lilly, tell them.

19:02.489 --> 19:04.926
[tense music]

19:04.969 --> 19:07.929
- Give me your cuffs.
- Why?

19:07.972 --> 19:09.626
- So I can lock her up.

19:09.670 --> 19:11.367
- You see a jail cell
around here?

19:11.411 --> 19:12.673
♪

19:12.716 --> 19:13.717
- We put her in that car
until we figure out

19:13.761 --> 19:15.284
what to do with her.

19:15.328 --> 19:18.635
- Sure about this, Sam?
- Yeah, I am.

19:18.679 --> 19:19.854
She attacked Ty.

19:19.897 --> 19:21.072
She's a threat
to everyone here,

19:21.116 --> 19:23.901
especially Lilly.

19:23.945 --> 19:25.251
Come on.

19:25.294 --> 19:29.907
- No, no, no, no, please.
Please don't do this.

19:31.257 --> 19:34.912
No, no, please. Please.

19:34.956 --> 19:38.699
- Listen, Marybeth.
We have to do this.

19:42.050 --> 19:43.747
- Hey, let's go for a walk.

19:43.791 --> 19:45.749
- [sobbing]

19:50.928 --> 19:55.150
[indistinct chatter]

19:56.891 --> 19:58.414
- Food has never
looked so good.

19:58.458 --> 20:00.199
- And we have plenty
we can send back with you.

20:02.418 --> 20:04.159
You're healing well.

20:04.203 --> 20:05.552
- Thanks to you.

20:05.595 --> 20:07.423
- We appreciate you taking
such good care of him.

20:07.467 --> 20:10.252
- It was my pleasure.

20:10.296 --> 20:12.602
- Finish up, Isaiah.

20:12.646 --> 20:15.126
You've got chores to do.

20:15.170 --> 20:19.957
- Can I show Eve the lake
before my chores? Please?

20:20.001 --> 20:21.568
- Fine.

20:21.611 --> 20:24.005
- You know, I would love to,
but the people in my clearing

20:24.048 --> 20:26.268
are really hungry,
and I need to get back to them.

20:26.312 --> 20:27.791
- It's going to take us
a few minutes

20:27.835 --> 20:30.054
to gather your supplies,
so you have a little time.

20:30.098 --> 20:32.622
Ty, would you like to join me?

20:33.493 --> 20:35.669
- Happy to.

20:35.712 --> 20:37.018
- Please, Eve?

20:44.373 --> 20:45.548
- Okay, I'll be right there.

20:45.592 --> 20:48.508
Give me a second.
What's going on?

20:48.551 --> 20:50.249
- I just can't ignore this,
Eve.

20:50.292 --> 20:52.207
I need to know if Silas
killed those people.

20:52.251 --> 20:53.426
- Levi.

20:53.469 --> 20:54.949
- Hey, we might leave here
with food today,

20:54.992 --> 20:56.603
but we'll still be
in danger tomorrow.

20:56.646 --> 20:58.648
- We just convinced Para
to help us.

20:58.692 --> 20:59.997
We go accusing Silas of murder

21:00.041 --> 21:01.651
we're going to leave here
with nothing.

21:01.695 --> 21:03.653
- I promise I won't say
anything unless I have proof.

21:03.697 --> 21:05.481
- And how are you
going to do that?

21:05.525 --> 21:08.223
- Take a look around
while you're with the kid.

21:08.267 --> 21:10.660
I don't find anything,
I drop it.

21:10.704 --> 21:14.273
Hey, I need you to trust me.

21:15.752 --> 21:17.798
- Be careful.

21:25.980 --> 21:27.111
- Thank you so much.

21:27.155 --> 21:28.896
Okay.

21:28.939 --> 21:31.855
[tense music]

21:31.899 --> 21:34.336
♪

21:34.380 --> 21:36.860
- [exhales]

21:36.904 --> 21:40.864
♪

21:40.908 --> 21:43.040
- My friend at DHS
is running the car's plates.

21:43.084 --> 21:46.348
We should have an address soon.

21:46.392 --> 21:48.350
You okay?

21:48.394 --> 21:52.833
- Another vision.
But it's different, clearer.

21:52.876 --> 21:54.791
- What did you see?

21:54.835 --> 21:57.316
- Eve and Levi
eating together at a table.

21:57.359 --> 21:58.578
- Well,
that's--that's good, right?

21:58.621 --> 22:01.494
It means they're safe.

22:01.537 --> 22:03.191
- It's complicated.

22:05.236 --> 22:08.457
Levi told me
that he had an affair with Eve.

22:10.720 --> 22:14.594
- Uh, I'm sorry, Gavin.

22:14.637 --> 22:16.160
- Nah, look,
if I'm being honest,

22:16.204 --> 22:19.033
you know,
it was my fault.

22:19.076 --> 22:23.385
I was in a bad place.
I--I pushed her away.

22:23.429 --> 22:26.780
- Maybe now you'll find a way
to make things right.

22:26.823 --> 22:29.739
[phone buzzes]

22:29.783 --> 22:33.134
- Yes.
This is Gavin Harris.

22:33.177 --> 22:35.136
She what?

22:35.179 --> 22:37.747
I think I might know
where she is.

22:37.791 --> 22:39.967
That was Izzy's principal.

22:40.010 --> 22:43.231
Izzy cut school.
I got to go find her.

22:43.274 --> 22:45.538
Call me when you get
Ella's address.

22:45.581 --> 22:49.759
[birds squawking]

22:54.373 --> 22:55.983
- I can see why you
like this place.

22:56.026 --> 22:58.246
- It's where my grandfather
taught me to fish.

22:58.289 --> 23:00.640
- Is it just you
and your grandfather?

23:00.683 --> 23:03.860
- My parents died
when I was young.

23:03.904 --> 23:06.472
- I'm so sorry.

23:06.515 --> 23:10.084
You know, I lost my father
a few years ago.

23:10.127 --> 23:13.174
- Do you miss him?
- Every day.

23:13.217 --> 23:15.132
Grew up together on a farm.
He loved the outdoors.

23:15.176 --> 23:16.743
He loved fishing too.

23:16.786 --> 23:19.180
- I wish I could
remember my parents.

23:19.223 --> 23:21.269
My grandfather doesn't like
to talk about them.

23:21.312 --> 23:24.751
- Sometimes it can be hard
to talk about people we lost.

23:24.794 --> 23:26.143
Do your parents have
any friends here,

23:26.187 --> 23:27.928
people who can share stories
about them?

23:27.971 --> 23:31.279
- No, no one knew them.
- They didn't live here?

23:31.322 --> 23:35.283
- No. Me and my grandfather
came here a few years ago.

23:35.326 --> 23:38.939
- Your grandfather's not
from the ship?

23:38.982 --> 23:41.115
Where's he from?

23:41.158 --> 23:43.552
- I'm not allowed
to talk about that.

23:45.249 --> 23:48.296
- Eve.
- Did you find anything?

23:48.339 --> 23:50.080
- I followed Silas.
When he left his hut,

23:50.124 --> 23:54.171
I went in and looked around
and found this.

23:54.215 --> 23:56.478
- Oh, my God. It's Eddie's.
- If he didn't do it,

23:56.522 --> 23:58.524
then why the hell
does he have his wallet?

23:58.567 --> 24:00.482
- Is everything okay, Eve?

24:00.526 --> 24:02.441
- Do me a favor
and stay here, okay?

24:02.484 --> 24:05.400
[tense music]

24:05.444 --> 24:09.099
♪

24:09.143 --> 24:13.930
- Para, we need to talk.

24:13.974 --> 24:17.804
- Found this in Silas' hut.

24:17.847 --> 24:20.894
- It's Eddie's,
our friend who died.

24:20.937 --> 24:25.507
♪

24:25.551 --> 24:29.511
- You don't understand.
- Para, everything all right?

24:29.555 --> 24:30.904
- No, it isn't.

24:30.947 --> 24:32.209
This wallet belonged
to a person

24:32.253 --> 24:35.778
in our clearing who died.
Why did you have it?

24:35.822 --> 24:39.521
- We have a witness
who saw you, can't deny it.

24:39.565 --> 24:43.394
- I don't. I was there.

24:43.438 --> 24:45.527
The man was dead
when I found him.

24:45.571 --> 24:47.529
We've been trying to figure out
where you're all from.

24:47.573 --> 24:50.706
So I searched the body
and found that.

24:50.750 --> 24:54.884
- You expect us to believe you?
- I believe him.

24:54.928 --> 24:58.584
Someone's out there killing
people, but it's not Silas.

24:58.627 --> 25:00.803
- How do you know that?
- Because I found another body

25:00.847 --> 25:03.850
in the woods with burn marks
just like your friend.

25:03.893 --> 25:07.549
Silas and I carried him
back here for a proper burial.

25:07.593 --> 25:09.116
- Is that what
the handprint was for?

25:09.159 --> 25:11.379
- Yes.
It's a symbol of protection,

25:11.422 --> 25:13.947
same as the one Silas
wears on his back.

25:13.990 --> 25:16.558
We opened our home to you,
offered you help,

25:16.602 --> 25:18.647
and you betrayed that trust.

25:18.691 --> 25:22.695
It's time for you to leave.
- Para, please.

25:22.738 --> 25:23.913
- You need to go.

25:23.957 --> 25:27.134
[horn blows]

25:27.177 --> 25:28.483
- What is that?

25:28.527 --> 25:29.919
- That horn only sounds
in emergencies.

25:29.963 --> 25:31.791
- Para! Para!
- What's happened?

25:31.834 --> 25:33.444
- It's Isaiah; he was taken.

25:33.488 --> 25:34.924
- Did you have something
to do with this?

25:34.968 --> 25:36.535
- No. God, no.
- It was a woman.

25:36.578 --> 25:38.101
She came out of the woods.
We tried to stop her.

25:38.145 --> 25:39.581
They were headed
towards the hills.

25:39.625 --> 25:41.409
- We need to send out
a search party right away.

25:41.452 --> 25:43.280
You head north.
I'll take the east.

25:43.324 --> 25:44.978
- Para, we'll help
you look for him.

25:45.021 --> 25:46.240
- Absolutely not.

25:46.283 --> 25:47.589
- The more eyes
out there the better.

25:47.633 --> 25:52.072
- It would be foolish not
to take our help.

25:52.115 --> 25:53.943
- They're right. Let's go.

25:59.209 --> 25:59.558
.

25:59.601 --> 26:02.648
[seagulls squawking]

26:08.828 --> 26:11.831
- Iz.
- What are you doing here?

26:11.874 --> 26:15.138
- School called,
said you cut class.

26:20.056 --> 26:22.711
When we used to visit
your Aunt Jessica,

26:22.755 --> 26:25.714
your mom used to want
to come straight to the water.

26:25.758 --> 26:29.065
This was her favorite spot.

26:29.109 --> 26:32.460
I don't know how many days
we spent sitting here together.

26:36.943 --> 26:39.772
- This morning,
who was that call from?

26:41.425 --> 26:43.689
- I told you; it was for a job.

26:43.732 --> 26:45.734
- Dad, please stop lying.

26:45.778 --> 26:47.649
I need you
to tell me the truth.

26:47.693 --> 26:49.869
Did you really give up
on Mom and Josh?

26:49.912 --> 26:54.613
- Iz, there's nothing else
we can do.

26:54.656 --> 26:56.963
- I don't believe you.
You never give up.

26:57.006 --> 26:59.139
That's what I've always
admired about you.

26:59.182 --> 27:01.750
After the accident,
when I was ready to quit,

27:01.794 --> 27:03.926
I thought about you and what
you were going through,

27:03.970 --> 27:06.059
that you were were fighting
through it every day.

27:06.102 --> 27:08.191
- Iz.
- I know you think this

27:08.235 --> 27:11.325
is what's best for me,
but you're wrong.

27:11.368 --> 27:14.241
- Hey, I wish I could tell you
I could bring them back,

27:14.284 --> 27:15.808
but I can't.

27:20.029 --> 27:21.901
At least not yet.

27:21.944 --> 27:26.427
- What do you mean, not yet?

27:26.470 --> 27:27.776
- The truth is,
it was Dr. Nathan

27:27.820 --> 27:29.212
who called this morning.

27:29.256 --> 27:31.954
We're not giving up.
I didn't want to tell you,

27:31.998 --> 27:34.217
because I don't know
where it could lead

27:34.261 --> 27:37.264
and I didn't want
to get your hopes up and--

27:37.307 --> 27:38.918
and not come through for you.

27:38.961 --> 27:40.528
- Dad.
- No, I saw what it did to you

27:40.571 --> 27:43.400
last time.
I don't want you to get hurt.

27:43.444 --> 27:45.272
- The only way we're going
to get through this

27:45.315 --> 27:50.146
is if we do it together.

27:50.190 --> 27:51.495
- Okay.

27:51.539 --> 27:55.412
Starting now,
that's what we do.

27:55.456 --> 27:58.024
- Good. So what's the plan?

27:58.067 --> 28:00.940
- Right now I'm waiting on
a call from Dr. Nathan.

28:00.983 --> 28:03.420
And I'll tell you everything
else on the way home.

28:03.464 --> 28:05.901
- Can we make a stop?

28:05.945 --> 28:09.688
This kid at school, Andrew, he
told me there's a vigil today.

28:09.731 --> 28:11.994
- Of course.

28:13.126 --> 28:14.301
Come on.

28:20.611 --> 28:24.354
- Ahh! Ahh!

28:24.398 --> 28:25.616
Let me out of here!

28:25.660 --> 28:27.227
Help!

28:30.926 --> 28:33.407
- Jesus.
- Open the door.

28:33.450 --> 28:35.757
- Please, just get me out.
- What the hell is going on?

28:35.801 --> 28:38.542
- Riley, please help me.
Your dad locked me up in here.

28:38.586 --> 28:40.762
- Okay, hang on.
I'll go talk to him.

28:40.806 --> 28:42.372
- You sure you want
to let her out?

28:42.416 --> 28:43.765
- What you'd rather leave her
chained to a steering wheel?

28:43.809 --> 28:45.158
- We start locking each other
in cars,

28:45.201 --> 28:47.551
things going to get
real bad around here.

28:47.595 --> 28:49.031
- I'll go find my dad.

28:49.075 --> 28:50.511
- You should understand.
All right?

28:50.554 --> 28:51.991
We had to secure the threat,
I secured the threat.

28:52.034 --> 28:53.557
- This isn't like you, Sam.

28:53.601 --> 28:55.298
- Marybeth,
I know what I'm doing.

28:55.342 --> 28:59.172
- Lilly, have you seen my dad?
- He's in there.

28:59.215 --> 29:01.783
- Look, I know she's done
some bad things.

29:01.827 --> 29:04.090
But we've got to have a plan.
- I'm working on it.

29:04.133 --> 29:06.396
- How about we let her go?
That sound like a plan?

29:06.440 --> 29:09.225
- Riley, I'll handle this.
- Dad, she's freaking out.

29:09.269 --> 29:11.619
You can't keep her locked up;
it's not right.

29:11.662 --> 29:13.186
- I got to side
with your kid here, Sam.

29:13.229 --> 29:14.317
- Thank you.

29:14.361 --> 29:16.232
- Look, I'm all
for law enforcement,

29:16.276 --> 29:18.408
but there's this thing about
cruel and unusual punishment.

29:18.452 --> 29:20.323
- I'm trying to keep us safe.

29:20.367 --> 29:23.849
- Hey! Hey!

29:23.892 --> 29:25.938
Something's wrong
with Veronica.

29:29.768 --> 29:32.205
- [gasping]

29:32.248 --> 29:34.163
- It's okay; we're going
to get you out of here.

29:34.207 --> 29:36.078
- What happened?
- She started hyperventilating.

29:36.122 --> 29:38.124
I think she's having
trouble breathing.

29:38.167 --> 29:39.821
- We need to get her
out of there.

29:39.865 --> 29:44.565
- Please, help her.
- Veronica, hold on. Hold on.

29:44.608 --> 29:46.828
Lucas, give me a hand.

29:46.872 --> 29:50.005
- [gasping]

29:50.049 --> 29:51.746
- What do we do?
- Dad.

29:51.790 --> 29:53.226
- Sam.
- Dad.

29:56.533 --> 29:57.970
- Veronica, can you hear me?

29:58.013 --> 29:59.493
Does she have
any medical conditions?

29:59.536 --> 30:00.973
- No, I don't think so.

30:01.016 --> 30:03.279
- Rapid pulse, shallow
breathing, dilated pupils.

30:03.323 --> 30:05.934
I think she's having
anxiety-induced anaphylaxis.

30:05.978 --> 30:07.196
Veronica,
we need to get control

30:07.240 --> 30:08.937
of your breathing, okay?

30:08.981 --> 30:11.287
Veronica, can you hear me?
Veronica, can you hear me?

30:11.331 --> 30:14.682
- Veronica!

30:14.725 --> 30:18.512
- She's not breathing.

30:18.555 --> 30:22.472
Come on, breathe, Veronica.

30:22.516 --> 30:24.735
Come on.

30:24.779 --> 30:27.564
Breathe Veronica, breathe!
- [gasps]

30:27.608 --> 30:29.262
- That's it. That's it.
That's it. That's it.

30:29.305 --> 30:31.830
Just breathe.
Just breathe.

30:31.873 --> 30:35.355
- [sobbing]

30:48.890 --> 30:49.935
- Excuse me.

30:49.978 --> 30:54.069
Hey.
- Izzy, I'm glad you came.

30:54.113 --> 30:56.985
- Thanks again for inviting me.
This is my dad.

30:57.029 --> 31:00.989
- Hey.
- This your family?

31:01.033 --> 31:02.861
- That's my father
and my sister.

31:04.688 --> 31:06.125
- They could argue like crazy,

31:06.168 --> 31:08.127
but it's only because
they're so much alike.

31:10.042 --> 31:14.046
- I know this is going
to sound weird, but--

31:14.089 --> 31:16.439
but part of me
still thinks they're alive.

31:16.483 --> 31:19.138
I just can't let it go.

31:19.181 --> 31:23.142
- Andrew.
- My mom just got here.

31:23.185 --> 31:25.666
I'll catch up
with you guys later.

31:25.709 --> 31:27.711
- What you said,

31:27.755 --> 31:30.845
I don't think
it's weird at all.

31:30.889 --> 31:33.326
If I were you,
I wouldn't give up hope, okay?

31:35.284 --> 31:39.375
- Thanks.

31:48.907 --> 31:51.822
- These are the people
we have to save, Dad.

31:51.866 --> 31:55.783
[phone buzzes]

31:55.826 --> 31:59.265
- Sophia.

32:01.093 --> 32:02.572
You're kidding.

32:02.616 --> 32:05.924
No, no, I can leave right now.

32:05.967 --> 32:08.056
I'll meet you there.

32:08.100 --> 32:10.058
- What did she say?
- Ella, the artist

32:10.102 --> 32:11.930
I was telling you about,

32:11.973 --> 32:15.020
she has a house
in Topanga Canyon.

32:15.063 --> 32:17.805
It's right near where
we were both found as kids.

32:19.154 --> 32:20.199
- You really think
she's the key

32:20.242 --> 32:21.852
to bringing Mom and Josh home?

32:21.896 --> 32:23.332
- There's only one way
to find out.

32:23.376 --> 32:25.595
Let's go.

32:25.639 --> 32:28.990
- Isaiah! Isaiah!

32:29.034 --> 32:32.298
Isaiah!
- Isaiah!

32:32.341 --> 32:34.822
- Let's split up,
search the area.

32:34.865 --> 32:36.998
- Yeah, I'll come with you.

32:37.042 --> 32:40.175
- Isaiah!
- Isaiah!

32:40.219 --> 32:41.742
- Isaiah!

32:41.785 --> 32:43.918
- Isaiah!

32:43.962 --> 32:48.749
- Isaiah!

32:48.792 --> 32:51.186
- Hey, look at this.

32:53.667 --> 32:56.626
- Isaiah's friends were playing
with this earlier.

32:56.670 --> 32:58.672
- There's another one.

32:58.715 --> 33:00.500
- He's leaving us a trail.

33:00.543 --> 33:01.805
- It's this way.

33:01.849 --> 33:05.418
- Come on.

33:05.461 --> 33:07.202
[tense music]

33:07.246 --> 33:10.640
- Please, stop. Let me go.

33:10.684 --> 33:12.120
[grunting]

33:12.164 --> 33:13.817
Please, I want to go home.

33:13.861 --> 33:14.949
Let me go.

33:14.993 --> 33:17.778
- Isaiah! Isaiah! Stop!

33:17.821 --> 33:21.738
♪

33:21.782 --> 33:25.525
- [grunting]

33:25.568 --> 33:27.570
Hello, Rebecca.

33:27.614 --> 33:29.572
♪

33:33.054 --> 33:33.402
.

33:33.446 --> 33:36.362
[tense music]

33:36.405 --> 33:39.626
Let him go now.

33:39.669 --> 33:42.585
- I can't do that.
- He belongs here with me.

33:42.629 --> 33:44.544
- You love him. I understand.

33:44.587 --> 33:46.154
But this isn't about
what you want.

33:46.198 --> 33:48.374
You know how important he is.

33:49.592 --> 33:51.072
- Grandpa,
what's she talking about?

33:51.116 --> 33:55.163
- It's okay, Isaiah.

33:55.207 --> 33:57.600
I won't let you
take him from me.

33:57.644 --> 33:59.950
It's your last warning,
Rebecca.

34:01.952 --> 34:05.521
Let him go.

34:06.827 --> 34:07.784
- Isaiah!

34:07.828 --> 34:10.918
- Ahh!

34:10.961 --> 34:12.050
- Isaiah!

34:12.093 --> 34:14.139
- Isaiah!

34:14.182 --> 34:17.142
[tense music]

34:17.185 --> 34:18.317
♪

34:18.360 --> 34:20.362
- Oh, my God.

34:22.582 --> 34:23.670
- We need to stop the bleeding.

34:23.713 --> 34:26.629
- The boy,
you need to find him.

34:26.673 --> 34:28.675
- Eve, what happened?

34:28.718 --> 34:32.287
- I don't know.
- Silas took him.

34:32.331 --> 34:34.985
He's not who you think he is.

34:35.029 --> 34:36.161
- Who are you?

34:36.204 --> 34:39.816
- You're Rebecca Aldridge,
aren't you?

34:39.860 --> 34:41.688
- We need to get her back
to the village now.

34:41.731 --> 34:45.692
- Wait. Please.
Silas, you have to stop him.

34:45.735 --> 34:46.910
- I'll go after them.
Wait.

34:46.954 --> 34:48.521
Wait, wait. How do you know
who she is?

34:48.564 --> 34:49.696
- I'll explain
everything later.

34:49.739 --> 34:52.481
Help them get her back
to the village.

34:52.525 --> 34:55.571
♪

35:06.365 --> 35:08.149
- How's Veronica?

35:08.193 --> 35:10.064
- She's resting, doing better.

35:10.108 --> 35:14.329
- Good.

35:14.373 --> 35:17.202
Dad...

35:17.245 --> 35:20.205
what happened today?

35:20.248 --> 35:22.120
- I'm not proud of what I did.

35:22.163 --> 35:24.426
Let's just leave it at that,
okay?

35:24.470 --> 35:26.907
- No, I'm sorry.
But that's not good enough.

35:26.950 --> 35:30.302
I've never seen you
act like that.

35:30.345 --> 35:31.564
Something's going on.

35:31.607 --> 35:35.176
- No, there isn't.

35:35.220 --> 35:37.744
- Fine. Lie to me.

35:37.787 --> 35:39.528
Why should 10,000 B.C.
change anything, right?

35:39.572 --> 35:41.051
- What's that supposed to mean?

35:44.881 --> 35:46.796
- [sighs]

35:46.840 --> 35:50.104
Dad,

35:50.148 --> 35:53.629
back home you never
talked to me about anything.

35:53.673 --> 35:56.937
You always keep this wall
up like you're super human,

35:56.980 --> 35:58.678
like nothing ever bothers you.

35:58.721 --> 36:02.943
Well, news flash, you're not
fooling anyone, okay?

36:02.986 --> 36:06.903
Please, just tell me
what's going on.

36:13.519 --> 36:17.697
- When I was in Afghanistan,

36:17.740 --> 36:22.745
things happened
that just stay with you.

36:25.357 --> 36:29.970
I came home.

36:30.013 --> 36:35.454
I tried to ignore it,
push through.

36:35.497 --> 36:39.066
But I couldn't.

36:39.109 --> 36:42.678
Sometimes I thought
I was still there.

36:44.680 --> 36:48.075
- You had PTSD.

36:48.118 --> 36:50.120
- Yeah.

36:50.164 --> 36:53.254
So I started
taking something for it.

36:53.298 --> 36:55.952
I've been on them for years.

36:55.996 --> 37:00.435
This morning
I lost my last pill.

37:00.479 --> 37:04.787
- Does Mom know?
- She's the only one.

37:04.831 --> 37:08.008
- How come you never told us?

37:08.051 --> 37:12.186
- I guess...

37:12.230 --> 37:13.492
I wanted you and Andrew
to keep thinking

37:13.535 --> 37:17.017
I was that superhero.

37:17.060 --> 37:21.674
I didn't want you knowing
something was wrong with me.

37:21.717 --> 37:27.027
- Dad, there is nothing wrong
with you.

37:27.070 --> 37:29.682
And hiding things
is not how you handle this.

37:29.725 --> 37:31.858
- I'm starting to realize that.

37:31.901 --> 37:35.078
- You can always
tell me the truth.

37:39.779 --> 37:43.043
- I'm scared, Riley.

37:43.086 --> 37:45.263
- We're going to figure
this out.

37:45.306 --> 37:48.091
- Okay.

37:56.796 --> 37:59.886
- Hey, anything?
- No, no sign of him.

37:59.929 --> 38:01.279
- Levi, how do you know her?

38:01.322 --> 38:05.544
- I don't.

38:05.587 --> 38:06.762
Look who's there.

38:06.806 --> 38:08.329
Rebecca Aldridge
designed the plane

38:08.373 --> 38:09.678
the Mojave Crew flew down in,

38:09.722 --> 38:11.376
but she wasn't part
of the exploratory team.

38:11.419 --> 38:15.118
- What's she doing down here?
- I have no idea.

38:15.162 --> 38:16.946
- Eve, Levi.

38:16.990 --> 38:18.731
- I was able to stop
the bleeding,

38:18.774 --> 38:20.689
but she's still very weak.

38:20.733 --> 38:23.692
I'm not sure if she'll make it.

38:23.736 --> 38:25.041
- Did she say anything?

38:25.085 --> 38:27.827
- Only that she wants
to talk to you.

38:39.317 --> 38:41.580
- Ella! Hello?

38:41.623 --> 38:42.972
- She's not here.

38:43.016 --> 38:46.628
- Well, we came this far;
let's look around.

38:46.672 --> 38:47.803
- Yeah.

39:03.210 --> 39:05.038
- What is it?

39:05.081 --> 39:09.651
- Something about this place
feels familiar,

39:09.695 --> 39:12.741
like I've been here before.

39:18.356 --> 39:20.793
- Gavin.

39:20.836 --> 39:23.622
What are you looking for?

39:23.665 --> 39:25.841
- I don't know yet.

39:37.505 --> 39:39.507
- You wanted to see me.

39:39.551 --> 39:41.074
- The boy is special.

39:41.117 --> 39:44.643
There's something he has to do.

39:44.686 --> 39:46.601
But Silas is trying to stop it.

39:46.645 --> 39:48.560
- What are you talking about?

39:48.603 --> 39:52.868
- Eve, you need to trust me.

39:52.912 --> 39:55.784
- How do you know who I am?
- It doesn't matter.

39:55.828 --> 40:00.615
- What's important
is that you find Isaiah.

40:00.659 --> 40:03.052
- Why? Why me?

40:03.096 --> 40:06.404
- You have no idea
who he is, do you?

40:07.970 --> 40:11.452
- Grandpa, why can't we
go back to the village?

40:11.496 --> 40:13.062
Why did you hurt that woman?

40:13.106 --> 40:14.324
- You have to trust me,
Isaiah.

40:14.368 --> 40:16.675
I'm doing this
because I love you.

40:16.718 --> 40:20.026
- She said something
strange, Grandpa.

40:20.069 --> 40:22.594
- That woman is full of lies.

40:22.637 --> 40:24.726
You can't believe
a thing she says.

40:29.862 --> 40:31.472
We need to clean your wound.

40:43.484 --> 40:44.920
- Look.

40:46.748 --> 40:49.621
- What is that?

40:49.664 --> 40:52.537
- It looks like a sinkhole,

40:52.580 --> 40:54.234
or it used to be one.

40:55.583 --> 41:01.459
- [gasping]

41:01.502 --> 41:04.070
- Grandpa...

41:04.113 --> 41:05.506
she said my name
wasn't Isaiah.

41:13.949 --> 41:15.429
Oh, my God.

41:15.473 --> 41:18.476
She said
my real name was Gavin.

41:18.519 --> 41:21.087
- I've had this scar
since I was little.

41:21.130 --> 41:24.177
I never knew
where it came from.

41:24.220 --> 41:27.267
- Dad, what are
you talking about?

41:27.310 --> 41:32.751
- I can't explain it,
but it's me

41:32.794 --> 41:35.014
when I was a kid.

41:39.671 --> 41:41.847
I'm in that place.

41:41.890 --> 41:44.197
- How is that possible?
- I'm not sure.

41:44.240 --> 41:48.593
But I don't think the things
I've been seeing are visions.

41:48.636 --> 41:53.685
They're memories.

41:53.728 --> 41:55.948
I think I'm from that world.

41:55.991 --> 41:58.951
- Isaiah is Gavin?

41:58.994 --> 42:02.911
- He is,
and he needs your help.

42:02.955 --> 42:06.175
[dramatic music]
